  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a large saucepan over medium heat.",
    "Add the diced onion and cook until translucent, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the minced garlic and cook for an additional 1 minute.",
    "Add the chopped nuka-pickle and cook for 2 minutes, stirring frequently.",
    "Add the chicken broth, salt, and black pepper, and bring to a boil.",
    "Reduce the heat to low and simmer for 10 minutes.",
    "Stir in the all purpose flour to thicken the pilaf.",
    "Cook for an additional 2 minutes, or until the pilaf has reached the desired consistency.",
    "Stir in the chopped parsley.",
    "Serve the pilaf on a talavera plate."
